# AMA-MIDI Project Brief

## Context

Amanotes needs a web-based internal tool to prototype MIDI sequences (piano-roll style) for game soundtracks. The tool visualizes notes across 8 tracks, with time flowing vertically (0s at top, 300s max at bottom).

## Use Cases

1. **Piano Roll Visualization**: Grid where X-axis = 8 Tracks, Y-axis = Time (0-300s). Notes rendered as circular points at precise (track, time) coordinates.
2. **Note Management**: CRUD operations on notes with properties: Title, Description, Track (1-8), Time (0-300), and Color.
3. **Sequence Integrity**: Prevent duplicate notes at the same (track, time) position.
4. **Collaborative Sequencing**: Multiple composers on the same Song, synchronized without double-writing or state corruption.

## Scoring Target: 90 / 100

| Category | Pts | Key Requirements |
|---|---|---|
| Foundation | 20 | CRUD for Songs/Notes, DB persistence, functional UI |
| Architecture | 10 | Clean React components, TypeScript, relational DB for Note/Song |
| Visualization & Integrity | 10 | Accurate piano roll grid, tests for positioning, atomic transactions |
| Security & Auth | 10 | Rate limiting, CSRF protection, SSO/OIDC or 2FA |
| UI/UX Excellence | 10 | Dark mode studio UI, responsive, snap-to-grid interactions |
| Advanced Backend | 10 | Real-time updates via WebSockets so multiple users see changes instantly |
| DevOps & Cloud | 10 | Dockerized, CI/CD pipeline, production hosting |
| Performance | 10 | Render 10,000+ notes efficiently, performance testing plan |
| ~~AI Innovation~~ | ~~10~~ | Skipped |

## Output Checklist

- Monorepo with clear `/apps/web` and `/apps/api` structure
- Ledger logic: MIDI changes tracked as a history of events (event sourcing)
- README with setup instructions, architectural diagrams, and trade-offs
- Test suite: conflict test (duplicate track+time), boundary test (time > 300s), performance test
